The National Union of Mineworkers is accusing government of siding with mining companies. The union says the Mineral Resources and Energy Department is useless, and has biased mining inspectors. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -Mineral Resources Minister, Gwede Mantashe, has hit back at the National Union of Mineworkers. He says the union has failed to exercise its right to approach him directly. On Wednesday, the NUM accused Mantashe's department of siding with mining companies. READ: NUM takes aim at Mineral Resources in battle for wages It is calling for a wage increase of at least 15 percent for three years. "I asked him (General-Secretary of the NUM) what are these grievances I am reading about because you have not talked to me in the last number of months," says Mantashe. Mantashe says that the department gave the union direction to call directly about there are issues. Watch the full interview above for more on this story.